                "1933,"
            ]
        ]
    ],
    "He spent two years as an independent scholar in Italy before immigrating to the United States where he joined New York University as a Professor at the Institute for Fine Arts in 1935.": [],
    "Recruited by the famous director, <a href=\"/cookw\">Walter W. S. Cook</a>.": [],
    "Lehmann also founded the Archaeological Research Fund at NYU.": [],
    "He continued his archaeological work in the Mediterranean, including the excavations of the Sanctuary of the Great Gods on the island of Samothrace begun in 1938 and continued after World War II.": [],
    "He became a United States citizen in 1944.": [],
    "Throughout his American career, he lectured and sat on dissertation committees.": [],
    "He was engaged in editing the Samothrace publications for the Bollingen Foundation in Switzerland at the time of his death.": [
